# Scenario-Based Planning (3–5 Year “Data Flywheel” Modeling)
Our model should explicitly capture how more users → more data → better model → lower costs / higher conversion → more users.
    – Data Flywheel Efficiency (DFE = % Improvement in Model Performance / % Increase in Data Volume)
    – Model Performance Index (Composite score (normalize to 0–1 or 0–100) --> MPI = w1*(Accuracy) + w2*(Latency Score) + w3*(Cost Efficiency Score))
    – Customer Acquisition Cost (CAC) Decay Rate
    – Data Network Effect Multiplier (DNEM --> Impact of cumulative data on growth: DNEM = 1 + log(Total Data / Initial Data))

# Cost Per Inference (CPI) Modeling (This is the AI-native COGS.)
    – Cost Per Inference (CPI = (Compute Cost + Model Licensing + Infrastructure Overhead) / # of Inferences)
    – Token-Level Economics (Cost per Token = Total Compute Cost / Total Tokens Processed)
    – Value per Token (Critical for AI unit economics. VPT = Revenue Attributable to Output / Tokens Used)
    – Gross Margin per Inference (GM_per_inference = Revenue_per_inference - CPI)
    – Model Cascading Efficiency --> Blended CPI with Cascading
        – Blended CPI = (% Small Model × Cost_small) + (% Medium Model × Cost_medium) + (% Large Model × Cost_large)
    – Routing Accuracy

# Synthetic Data Modeling: Include the cost and impact of synthetic data generation to fill data gaps for model training.
Synthetic data is both a cost center and a performance multiplier.
    – Synthetic Data Cost Ratio (SDCR = Synthetic Data Cost / Total Training Data Cost)
    – Data Coverage Ratio (How much of our problem space is covered.--> Coverage = (Real Data + Synthetic Data) / Total Required Data)
    – Performance Lift from Synthetic Data (Synthetic Lift (%) = (Model Performance_with_synth - without_synth) / without_synth)
    – Cost Efficiency of Synthetic Data (Cost per Performance Point = Synthetic Data Cost / Performance Improvement (%))
    – "Real Data" Ratio to Synthetic Data
    – Data Quality Score (Weighted measure: DQS = w1*(Realism) + w2*(Diversity) + w3*(Label Accuracy))

# Regulatory / Risk Adjustments
We need to discount (20%- 30%) projections to reflect compliance risk (e.g., EU AI Act, General Data Protection Regulation).
    – Revenue Risk Adjustment (Risk-Adjusted Revenue = Projected Revenue × (1 - Risk Discount))
    – Compliance Cost Ratio (Compliance Cost Ratio = Compliance Costs / Revenue)
    – Regulatory Exposure Score (RES)
        RES = w1*(Data Sensitivity) + w2*(Geographic Exposure) + w3*(Model Risk Level)
    – Expected Regulatory Impact (ERI = Probability of Regulation Event × Impact (Revenue Loss or Cost Increase))
    – Adjusted Gross Margin --> Adjusted GM = (Revenue × (1 - Risk Discount)) - (COGS + Compliance Costs)

# Agentic AI Metrics (Product Sophistication Premium)
Investors are increasingly moving away from basic LLM wrappers toward Agentic AI—solutions with autonomous, repeatable workflows.
--> What is our automation depth, because of applying Agentic workflows?
    – Agentic Depth Score (ADS = w1*(Task Autonomy) + w2*(Workflow Repeatability) + w3*(Decision Complexity))
        Where: Task Autonomy = % tasks completed without human input; Workflow Repeatability = % tasks reusable across customers; Decision Complexity = multi-step reasoning capability
    – Human-in-the-Loop Reduction Rate (HITL Reduction (%) = (Manual Steps_before - Manual Steps_after) / Manual Steps_before))
    – Automation Value per Customer (Automation Value = hours saved × Cost per hour)
    – Agent Reliability Score (Reliability = successful task completions / total executions)
    – Agentic Premium Factor (Maps product quality to valuation uplift: Adjusted Multiple = Base Multiple × (1 + Agentic Premium))
        Typical: Weak agent → 0–10%; Strong agent → 20–50%+;

# Vertical AI / Context Moat Metrics (defensibility via domain specificity)
    – Vertical Depth Score (VDS = w1*(Domain-specific features %) + w2*(Custom workflows) + w3*(Industry integrations))
    – Context Moat Strength
        Captures how hard it is to replicate your data + logic: (CMS = (Proprietary Data Volume × Data Uniqueness × Switching Cost))
    – Data Exclusivity Ratio (Exclusivity = Proprietary Data / Total Data Used)
    – Time-to-Replicate (TTR = Estimated months for competitor to match product)
    – Vertical Premium Multiplier (Adjusted Valuation = Base Valuation × (1 + Vertical Premium))
        Typical: Horizontal AI → baseline; Deep vertical → +25% to +100%

# Technical Team Premium Metrics
    – Team Premium Factor (TPF = Final Valuation / Baseline Valuation)
        Benchmark: Strong team → 2x to 5x (200–500%)
    – Founder Signal Score (FSS = w1*(Research pedigree) + w2*(Prior exits) + w3*(Relevant domain expertise))
    – Execution Credibility Index (ECI = (Shipped Products + Revenue Traction + Hiring Quality) / Time)
    – Talent Density Ratio (Talent Density = # Senior Engineers / Total Team Size)
    – Hiring Magnetism Score (Hiring Magnetism = Inbound candidates / Total hires) --> (High = strong brand + network)
     
